latestPosts.caption:
In a country where tradition and transformation co-exist, these castles say it all 🏯🎌

Samurai battles to WWII air raids, Osaka Castle has been destroyed and rebuilt more than once. A bold reconstruction, layered with centuries of ambition, power, and resilience. 

Himeji Castle, on the other hand, was never destroyed by war, earthquake or fire. Built in 1609 — and still standing strong as one of the country’s twelve original castles - a symbol of Japanese endurance!
.
